  carbohydrates: 98 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 21 g
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Place the @flour tortillas{4} on a #baking sheet{} and bake for about ~{4%minutes}, until crispy. Set aside. Meanwhile, slice the @zucchini{1} into 1/2-inch rounds. Core, seed, and remove the white veins from the @poblano pepper{1}, then thinly slice.

Toss zucchini and poblanos with @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Spread out on the same baking sheet you used for tortillas and roast for ~{20%minutes} in the oven, tossing halfway through.

Meanwhile halve and pit the @avocado{1}. Scoop out the flesh with a spoon and cube. Peel, halve, and finely chop the @red onion{1}. Cube the @tomato{1}, removing the tough core. Halve the @lime{1}.

Combine the tomato, onion, and avocado in a #bowl{} and drizzle with @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, juice of half the lime, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside.

In a #small pot{}, heat up the @black beans{1%can} and their liquid with a pinch of @salt{pinch} over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally. Once warmed through, mash with a #fork{}.

Spread some mashed beans on the crispy tortillas. Sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup} and top with roasted veggies. Place in the oven for about ~{5%minutes}, until cheese has melted.

Top the tostadas with tomato and avocado salsa and a dollop of @sour cream{2%tablespoon}.